1
00:00:16,789 --> 00:00:18,123
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:22,211
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,706 --> 00:00:59,707
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,790 --> 00:01:01,125
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:19,727 --> 00:01:21,061
YOO JAE-HA
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

6
00:01:21,145 --> 00:01:23,772
Oh. Do you wanna listen to it first?

7
00:01:23,856 --> 00:01:25,816
That's okay. I'll do it after you.

8
00:01:28,652 --> 00:01:29,778
Well, then.

9
00:01:30,863 --> 00:01:32,156
So, I…

10
00:01:34,658 --> 00:01:37,620
I'd like to apologize
if I crossed the line.

11
00:01:40,789 --> 00:01:42,082
Don't worry about it.

12
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:43,500
It's in the past now.

13
00:01:48,130 --> 00:01:49,465
Do you like Yoo Jae-ha?

14
00:01:49,548 --> 00:01:50,925
YOO JAE-HA
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

15
00:01:51,675 --> 00:01:52,676
Yes.

16
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:57,181
"Because I Love You" is my favorite song.
Which one do you like the most?

17
00:01:57,264 --> 00:01:59,183
That one's my favorite song too.

18
00:02:01,143 --> 00:02:02,519
When I come here,

19
00:02:02,603 --> 00:02:04,229
I always listen to it on vinyl.

20
00:02:04,313 --> 00:02:08,192
The remastered CD version
feels oddly slower,

21
00:02:08,275 --> 00:02:09,443
so it's not the same.

22
00:02:09,944 --> 00:02:10,945
[inhales deeply]

23
00:02:11,028 --> 00:02:14,448
I heard it was a technical error
from when it was transferred to CD.

24
00:02:14,949 --> 00:02:17,201
Oh, so that's why.

25
00:02:17,284 --> 00:02:19,411
It happened by pure coincidence,

26
00:02:19,495 --> 00:02:22,498
but I do think the change suits
a breakup song better.

27
00:02:23,207 --> 00:02:25,125
"I will give you everything I have

28
00:02:25,751 --> 00:02:27,836
now that you've come back to me."

29
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:30,631
It's about breaking up
and getting back together, no?

30
00:02:31,215 --> 00:02:35,010
It's more about his regret
and what he wishes he could do.

31
00:02:36,053 --> 00:02:41,308
[Jae-ha] ♪ But now I realize ♪

32
00:02:42,518 --> 00:02:49,274
♪ I belong to you only ♪

33
00:02:49,858 --> 00:02:56,824
♪ Now that you have returned to me ♪

34
00:03:00,035 --> 00:03:01,286
♪ I will give you everything… ♪

35
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:02,913
Now that I hear it that way,

36
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:05,290
it really does sound different.

37
00:03:10,254 --> 00:03:11,422
I guess…

38
00:03:12,881 --> 00:03:14,800
I haven't been able to let you go.

39
00:03:18,303 --> 00:03:23,976
♪ We will never say goodbye ♪

40
00:03:24,059 --> 00:03:26,186
YEONG-MOOK REPAIR SERVICES

41
00:03:28,355 --> 00:03:34,361
♪ Because I love only you ♪

42
00:03:36,363 --> 00:03:38,115
Oh. Hi, Mr. Kang!

43
00:03:38,198 --> 00:03:41,285
♪ Because I love you ♪

44
00:03:43,495 --> 00:03:44,747
[song ends]

45
00:03:47,499 --> 00:03:49,209
Did you come here a lot as a kid?

46
00:03:50,002 --> 00:03:53,505
Yeah. When I bombed a test
or didn't wanna go to tutoring,

47
00:03:53,589 --> 00:03:54,757
I usually hid out here.

48
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:58,218
Oh, we might've even run
into each other here, don't you think?

49
00:03:58,302 --> 00:03:59,595
Well, I think that

50
00:03:59,678 --> 00:04:02,264
I ran into a schoolgirl
who looked like a complete handful.

51
00:04:02,347 --> 00:04:06,143
And I think I remember seeing
an older guy who seemed incredibly boring.

52
00:04:06,226 --> 00:04:07,519
That probably wasn't me.

53
00:04:07,603 --> 00:04:09,772
People always said that
just being near me was pretty fun.

54
00:04:09,855 --> 00:04:12,775
-[scoffs, chortles]
-[chuckles]

55
00:04:12,858 --> 00:04:14,193
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

56
00:04:19,406 --> 00:04:20,449
[mouthing]

57
00:04:21,325 --> 00:04:23,368
That's just the store next door opening.

58
00:04:24,036 --> 00:04:25,996
[sighs] That scared me.

59
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,247
I thought it was my dad.

60
00:04:27,331 --> 00:04:30,250
Well, don't you think
we should tell your father, though?

61
00:04:30,334 --> 00:04:31,710
He'll probably feel betrayed.

62
00:04:32,336 --> 00:04:33,837
That's true, but…

63
00:04:34,838 --> 00:04:36,298
He's a good kid.

64
00:04:36,882 --> 00:04:38,550
And also a lonely one.

65
00:04:38,634 --> 00:04:41,553
What would you think
if I dated someone like him?

66
00:04:41,637 --> 00:04:43,472
[inhales deeply, sighs]

67
00:04:43,555 --> 00:04:44,556
I don't know.

68
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:47,351
You said he's a good guy. Why hesitate?

69
00:04:47,434 --> 00:04:49,812
That's a different story.

70
00:04:50,395 --> 00:04:52,940
I don't think the time is right just yet.

71
00:04:53,023 --> 00:04:54,733
Then let me know when the time is right.

72
00:04:55,526 --> 00:04:56,652
Okay.

73
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:03,075
-It's all set. Wanna listen?
-Yes.

74
00:05:10,707 --> 00:05:11,708
Wow.

75
00:05:14,628 --> 00:05:17,089
[distorted music playing]

76
00:05:17,172 --> 00:05:19,049
[classical song playing]

77
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,301
[gasps] It works!

78
00:05:22,427 --> 00:05:23,428
[sighs]

79
00:05:26,765 --> 00:05:28,809
It sounds just like it used to.

80
00:05:29,643 --> 00:05:31,478
It sounds so beautiful.

81
00:05:31,562 --> 00:05:33,564
[song continues]

82
00:05:40,988 --> 00:05:43,073
I know a photo can't capture sound,

83
00:05:43,157 --> 00:05:44,950
but let's take one as a keepsake.

84
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:46,618
[chuckles] Sure.

85
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:54,168
[camera shutter clicking]

86
00:05:55,294 --> 00:06:01,175
EPISODE 10 - DON'T KNOW
THE ANSWER, STILL CLOCKING IN!

87
00:06:01,258 --> 00:06:04,887
An in-store display?
Have you thought of any ideas?

88
00:06:04,970 --> 00:06:09,224
Usually, products from different companies
are displayed in one space.

89
00:06:09,308 --> 00:06:11,393
However, for Home-AI products,

90
00:06:11,476 --> 00:06:14,313
it's the best that we show them
all together at the same time.

91
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,065
Then we may have to
create a separate space

92
00:06:17,149 --> 00:06:19,526
for SAEUM Home-AI zone.

93
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:23,447
I'm not sure whether that will be possible
under the current agreement.

94
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:24,615
We understand that.

95
00:06:25,115 --> 00:06:27,868
We wanted to speak to you first
about the possibility.

96
00:06:27,951 --> 00:06:30,162
A Home-AI zone…

97
00:06:30,245 --> 00:06:31,246
Well,

98
00:06:31,788 --> 00:06:34,374
please send me a proposal,
and I'll discuss it internally.

99
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:36,919
Okay. I will send it to you right away.

100
00:06:37,002 --> 00:06:40,380
You never take an easy route,
Mr. Kang, do you?

101
00:06:41,256 --> 00:06:42,549
I'll take that as a compliment.

102
00:06:44,676 --> 00:06:47,554
Uh, should I reach out to the domestic
stores with the same proposal?

103
00:06:47,638 --> 00:06:50,182
Yes, let's do it on the condition
that we handle

104
00:06:50,265 --> 00:06:52,351
the system integration
and content updates.

105
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:53,977
I'll take care of the overseas account.

106
00:06:54,061 --> 00:06:56,480
Ms. Cha, Mr. Jeon,
please take care of the domestic side.

107
00:06:56,563 --> 00:06:57,648
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

108
00:06:57,731 --> 00:07:01,443
Also, I have a business trip
out of town today.

109
00:07:01,526 --> 00:07:02,903
-A business trip?
-Yes.

110
00:07:02,986 --> 00:07:06,573
An international buyer who couldn't attend
the demo requested a meeting.

111
00:07:07,074 --> 00:07:09,952
That's why I'll be in Pohang
today and tomorrow.

112
00:07:10,035 --> 00:07:12,704
Please make sure things run smoothly
while I'm away.

113
00:07:12,788 --> 00:07:13,789
Yes, sir.

114
00:07:13,872 --> 00:07:15,290
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

115
00:07:26,093 --> 00:07:27,094
[sighs]

116
00:07:27,719 --> 00:07:30,847
Hey, what is it?
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

117
00:07:30,931 --> 00:07:32,182
Did something happen?

118
00:07:32,266 --> 00:07:34,184
It's the Legal Team.

119
00:07:34,268 --> 00:07:36,853
I wrote "world's first"
'cause that's exactly what it is,

120
00:07:36,937 --> 00:07:38,563
but now they're demanding proof for it.

121
00:07:38,647 --> 00:07:39,898
What kind of proof?

122
00:07:39,982 --> 00:07:41,525
As far as we know, it's the world's first.

123
00:07:41,608 --> 00:07:42,943
That's what I'm saying.

124
00:07:43,527 --> 00:07:46,363
Get this, they asked if I had
combed through every tiny start-up

125
00:07:46,446 --> 00:07:49,074
in Africa to double-check. [scoffs] Geez.

126
00:07:49,157 --> 00:07:51,076
You know how conservative they are.

127
00:07:51,159 --> 00:07:53,120
No explanation will ever convince them,

128
00:07:53,203 --> 00:07:54,997
-so just change the wording.
-[sighs]

129
00:07:55,497 --> 00:07:57,165
They're seriously the worst.

130
00:07:57,249 --> 00:07:59,626
Hey, do you have a lead
for the web drama series?

131
00:07:59,710 --> 00:08:01,586
[exhales sharply] It's Cho Ga-eul.

132
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:03,171
[Kee-tae] Who's this Ga-eul?

133
00:08:03,255 --> 00:08:04,256
[Na-ri] It's Cho Ga-eul.

134
00:08:04,339 --> 00:08:05,507
Cho Ga-eul?

135
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:09,511
[Na-ri] Well, he's the singer of that band
that's blowing up right now.

136
00:08:10,721 --> 00:08:11,972
You know him, right?

137
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:15,309
Mmm. That's great.

138
00:08:15,392 --> 00:08:16,393
Isn't it?

139
00:08:16,476 --> 00:08:17,894
-[phone buzzing]
-[sighs]

140
00:08:17,978 --> 00:08:20,689
If it weren't for that Legal Team,
everything would be fine.

141
00:08:20,772 --> 00:08:24,109
Yay, I need to rewrite the PR material
from scratch. [laughs]

142
00:08:24,192 --> 00:08:25,402
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

143
00:08:25,485 --> 00:08:27,321
[Si-woo] Be the Clock-out Fairy today.

144
00:08:30,657 --> 00:08:33,076
I'm clocking out right on the dot today.

145
00:08:34,077 --> 00:08:35,996
Look at her bolt
the second Mr. Kang's gone.

146
00:08:36,079 --> 00:08:37,581
Well, I'm out of here too.

147
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:39,291
Seriously?

148
00:08:42,419 --> 00:08:44,463
-Later.
-For real?

149
00:08:44,546 --> 00:08:47,883
Hope you wrap it up quickly
and go home too… too… too…

150
00:08:47,966 --> 00:08:49,843
Wow, so much for loyalty.

151
00:08:51,511 --> 00:08:53,722
How am I gonna rewrite all this?

152
00:08:53,805 --> 00:08:55,098
[phone buzzing]

153
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:59,478
-Mr. Kang?
-[Si-woo] Have you left the office?

154
00:08:59,561 --> 00:09:01,938
Yes, I'm on my way home now.

155
00:09:02,481 --> 00:09:03,482
And what about you?

156
00:09:03,982 --> 00:09:05,275
I'm in Busan right now.

157
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,402
You're not in Pohang?

158
00:09:07,486 --> 00:09:08,653
No.

159
00:09:08,737 --> 00:09:12,157
An old classmate reached out to me,
saying he was down in Busan.

160
00:09:12,949 --> 00:09:14,868
I came right after my Pohang meeting.

161
00:09:14,951 --> 00:09:17,871
He must be a pretty close friend
to rush all the way down to Busan.

162
00:09:17,954 --> 00:09:20,624
He threatened me, saying he was debating
whether to sign with us.

163
00:09:20,707 --> 00:09:21,750
Ah.

164
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:23,251
So it's just business?

165
00:09:23,335 --> 00:09:27,297
I'm here doing sales for the team,
Sr. Associate Cha.

166
00:09:28,465 --> 00:09:31,385
Hmm. Well, you keep up
the good work, Manager Kang.

167
00:09:31,468 --> 00:09:33,178
I'll call you when I'm at the hotel.

168
00:09:33,678 --> 00:09:34,971
Okay.

169
00:09:37,849 --> 00:09:39,476
Who was that? Soo-jin?

170
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:41,645
No, my girlfriend.

171
00:09:41,728 --> 00:09:43,021
Mmm.

172
00:09:43,105 --> 00:09:44,106
Huh?

173
00:09:44,689 --> 00:09:45,690
What the…

174
00:09:46,274 --> 00:09:50,320
Choi Soo-jin and I divorced
a year after we got married.

175
00:09:50,404 --> 00:09:51,405
Wow.

176
00:09:51,988 --> 00:09:53,073
I had no idea.

177
00:09:54,366 --> 00:09:57,077
I put my foot in my mouth
big time with Soo-jin.

178
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,996
I asked how she was liking
working with her husband.

179
00:10:00,872 --> 00:10:02,040
She'll understand.

180
00:10:04,084 --> 00:10:05,293
But why did you split up?

181
00:10:05,377 --> 00:10:07,838
You two never fought once the entire time.

182
00:10:07,921 --> 00:10:10,090
Everyone was so jealous
and called you a rare match.

183
00:10:10,173 --> 00:10:11,299
Was that so?

184
00:10:15,011 --> 00:10:18,390
[inhales deeply] So you two
are just colleagues now?

185
00:10:19,015 --> 00:10:20,016
Mmm.

186
00:10:20,725 --> 00:10:22,561
She actually got remarried recently.

187
00:10:23,145 --> 00:10:24,229
And you?

188
00:10:24,312 --> 00:10:27,357
Are you dating your current girlfriend
with marriage in mind too?

189
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:29,901
[chuckles]

190
00:10:30,485 --> 00:10:32,654
[police siren blares]

191
00:10:34,239 --> 00:10:35,240
Hmm?

192
00:10:42,664 --> 00:10:44,291
Oh, you're back.

193
00:10:44,374 --> 00:10:45,834
Is something going on?

194
00:10:45,917 --> 00:10:47,919
A burglar broke into our building.

195
00:10:48,003 --> 00:10:49,004
A burglar?

196
00:10:49,087 --> 00:10:50,464
My unit got hit too.

197
00:10:51,047 --> 00:10:53,049
You'd better go inside
and check your place.

198
00:10:53,133 --> 00:10:54,217
Let's go on in, ma'am.

199
00:10:54,718 --> 00:10:55,927
Sorry?

200
00:11:04,394 --> 00:11:06,229
-Let's get some photos first.
-Sure.

201
00:11:06,938 --> 00:11:07,939
[gasps]

202
00:11:08,773 --> 00:11:10,775
[phone camera clicking]

203
00:11:11,818 --> 00:11:12,903
[sighs]

204
00:11:29,336 --> 00:11:32,088
[Ji-yoon] Someone broke into my place.

205
00:11:37,010 --> 00:11:38,345
[sighs]

206
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,603
[Si-woo] Ji-yoon,
you should go over to my place.

207
00:11:53,902 --> 00:11:56,488
When you get there,
have some warm tea first.

208
00:11:57,239 --> 00:11:59,783
The light-blue container
is the one with chamomile.

209
00:11:59,866 --> 00:12:00,867
CHAMOMILE

210
00:12:02,661 --> 00:12:04,871
[soothing music playing]

211
00:12:06,122 --> 00:12:09,000
[Si-woo] Then make yourself at home
and get some rest.

212
00:12:09,709 --> 00:12:11,086
You'll be safe there.

213
00:12:12,379 --> 00:12:13,672
[sighs deeply]

214
00:12:13,755 --> 00:12:15,131
It's so warm.

215
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,511
[sighs]

216
00:12:30,313 --> 00:12:31,731
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME LAUGH

217
00:12:31,815 --> 00:12:32,983
[Ji-yoon] What does…

218
00:12:33,692 --> 00:12:34,818
that mean?

219
00:12:37,862 --> 00:12:41,241
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME LAUGH

220
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:51,668
[sighs deeply]

221
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:56,381
[door closes]

222
00:13:00,468 --> 00:13:01,469
Ji-yoon?

223
00:13:04,472 --> 00:13:06,391
KANG SI-WOO
MAKES ME LAUGH TOO!

224
00:13:06,474 --> 00:13:08,560
[Ji-yoon] Kang Si-woo makes me laugh too!

225
00:13:09,936 --> 00:13:11,479
-[door opens]
-[chuckles]

226
00:13:14,232 --> 00:13:15,775
Oh, Mr. Kang.

227
00:13:16,901 --> 00:13:18,445
How did you get here at this hour?

228
00:13:19,029 --> 00:13:21,948
I almost missed the last train.
You must've been terrified.

229
00:13:24,868 --> 00:13:25,869
Yes.

230
00:13:26,536 --> 00:13:29,122
So you'll have to forgive me
for wearing your clothes.

231
00:13:29,664 --> 00:13:31,333
I was so scared I forgot to pack mine.

232
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:33,835
As long as you're safe,
nothing else matters.

233
00:13:33,918 --> 00:13:36,254
[chuckles] I feel very safe.

234
00:13:37,422 --> 00:13:38,506
[chuckles]

235
00:13:41,051 --> 00:13:43,386
Don't tell me you had to drop everything
because of me?

236
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:45,263
Do I look like someone who would do that?

237
00:13:46,264 --> 00:13:47,599
[chuckles] You don't.

238
00:13:48,516 --> 00:13:50,310
Thank you for coming so soon.

239
00:13:50,393 --> 00:13:51,811
Ji-yoon,

240
00:13:53,146 --> 00:13:54,773
stay here for the time being.

241
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,151
I'll be too worried if you don't.

242
00:13:58,234 --> 00:14:00,820
While you're staying here,
we can look for a new place for you.

243
00:14:02,989 --> 00:14:04,324
Am I moving in?

244
00:14:05,241 --> 00:14:06,451
I'd like it if you did.

245
00:14:07,077 --> 00:14:10,664
[chuckles] I was planning to move
once my lease is up anyway.

246
00:14:12,082 --> 00:14:13,166
Even before the break-in?

247
00:14:14,334 --> 00:14:15,543
Yes.

248
00:14:15,627 --> 00:14:18,630
I wanted to start making new memories
in a new place.

249
00:14:21,758 --> 00:14:22,801
Don't move too far away.

250
00:14:23,468 --> 00:14:24,594
Of course not.

251
00:14:25,095 --> 00:14:27,347
I plan on sticking right by your side.

252
00:14:52,789 --> 00:14:53,957
[sighs]

253
00:14:58,128 --> 00:15:01,589
Yeah. It'd be great to do it at my place,

254
00:15:01,673 --> 00:15:03,967
but we have a patient here. [chuckling]

255
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:05,844
Oh, please.

256
00:15:05,927 --> 00:15:09,180
Of course I'll prep the green onions
and garlic before bringing them over.

257
00:15:09,264 --> 00:15:10,348
Yeah.

258
00:15:15,437 --> 00:15:16,980
I'll have to call you back.

259
00:15:21,484 --> 00:15:22,652
You're home early.

260
00:15:23,236 --> 00:15:24,195
[bag thuds]

261
00:15:25,947 --> 00:15:27,115
What is this?

262
00:15:27,198 --> 00:15:28,450
What?

263
00:15:35,206 --> 00:15:36,958
Am I a joke to you?

264
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:39,461
[sighs, grunts]

265
00:15:40,879 --> 00:15:43,131
I told you to keep the cast on, didn't I?

266
00:15:43,214 --> 00:15:45,300
You need to leave it on
if you want it to heal!

267
00:15:45,383 --> 00:15:49,220
How else are we finally going to make it
to that lawyer's office?

268
00:15:50,180 --> 00:15:51,556
[both sigh]

269
00:15:55,435 --> 00:15:56,686
Let's see now,

270
00:15:57,437 --> 00:15:59,105
were you trying to wrap this or unwrap it?

271
00:15:59,189 --> 00:16:00,565
Unbelievable.

272
00:16:01,065 --> 00:16:02,776
[sighs deeply]

273
00:16:04,861 --> 00:16:08,364
I'm making kimchi over at
the laundromat lady's place tomorrow,

274
00:16:09,073 --> 00:16:11,367
so you and Joon-su
can order noodles or something.

275
00:16:11,451 --> 00:16:13,912
-Shouldn't I come along and help out?
-[laughs]

276
00:16:13,995 --> 00:16:15,330
In this state? No way.

277
00:16:17,874 --> 00:16:21,252
You can just take Ji-yoon some of
the kimchi once you're out of your cast.

278
00:16:23,087 --> 00:16:24,547
[grunts]

279
00:16:28,426 --> 00:16:30,386
[sighs] By the way,

280
00:16:31,554 --> 00:16:33,264
is something going on with Ji-yoon?

281
00:16:33,348 --> 00:16:34,474
Why?

282
00:16:34,557 --> 00:16:35,642
I don't know.

283
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:38,311
She seems to have a lot on her mind.

284
00:16:39,854 --> 00:16:40,855
Is she dating?

285
00:16:42,565 --> 00:16:46,194
It was a bit weird when she asked me
what kind of guy I'd like her to…

286
00:16:48,905 --> 00:16:50,406
Wait, what if she's dating some moron?

287
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:51,533
A moron?

288
00:16:52,116 --> 00:16:54,869
What if he's a kid Joon-su's age?
Or a total slacker,

289
00:16:54,953 --> 00:16:56,663
a divorcé, or the kind of…

290
00:16:57,247 --> 00:16:59,123
guy she's too embarrassed to talk about?

291
00:16:59,207 --> 00:17:00,959
[groans]

292
00:17:01,042 --> 00:17:02,877
See what you can find out
when you drop off the kimchi.

293
00:17:02,961 --> 00:17:04,796
-Should I?
-Uh-huh.

294
00:17:04,879 --> 00:17:07,423
-Okay. Got it.
-Mm-hmm.

295
00:17:08,758 --> 00:17:10,218
[grunts, sighs]

296
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:14,347
You can peel some garlic if you're bored.

297
00:17:16,391 --> 00:17:17,392
Mmm.

298
00:17:19,269 --> 00:17:22,772
This here is the absolute last one.

299
00:17:22,856 --> 00:17:25,942
I wasn't going to show you this one
because it's way over your budget,

300
00:17:26,025 --> 00:17:28,695
but since this gentleman here
is being incredibly particular,

301
00:17:28,778 --> 00:17:30,154
I had no choice.

302
00:17:30,655 --> 00:17:32,991
This place faces south,

303
00:17:33,074 --> 00:17:35,827
the neighbors are good,
security cameras are everywhere,

304
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:37,996
and it has great water pressure.

305
00:17:38,079 --> 00:17:40,707
If you can stretch your budget
to match the price, take it.

306
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,750
I just don't think I can walk anymore.

307
00:17:42,834 --> 00:17:44,669
I'll just look around for myself.

308
00:17:44,752 --> 00:17:45,920
Sure.

309
00:17:46,838 --> 00:17:51,551
Gosh, your husband is so thorough,
isn't he?

310
00:17:51,634 --> 00:17:52,760
[chuckles]

311
00:17:52,844 --> 00:17:55,847
But, you know,
if a man like that is only lenient to you,

312
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:58,433
he's a keeper. [chuckles]

313
00:17:59,309 --> 00:18:00,643
[door closes]

314
00:18:01,311 --> 00:18:04,480
Great. The water pressure's fine,
and the soundproofing is good.

315
00:18:04,564 --> 00:18:06,190
-However…
-What is it now?

316
00:18:06,274 --> 00:18:08,276
There are many dummy cameras these days.

317
00:18:08,359 --> 00:18:09,986
Are you sure the cameras here work?

318
00:18:10,069 --> 00:18:12,697
I'll head to the management office
and check with them myself.

319
00:18:13,573 --> 00:18:15,950
You two keep looking around. [sighs]

320
00:18:16,034 --> 00:18:17,035
Geez.

321
00:18:21,956 --> 00:18:22,999
Wow.

322
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:26,586
This place gets
really great natural light.

323
00:18:27,962 --> 00:18:31,132
Yes. Of all the places we saw today,
this is the best one.

324
00:18:31,215 --> 00:18:33,259
It's much more expensive, though.

325
00:18:33,343 --> 00:18:36,429
Besides, it's a little too big
to live in alone.

326
00:18:39,766 --> 00:18:42,602
Then, how about if we live together?

327
00:18:43,186 --> 00:18:44,354
-What?
-We could live here,

328
00:18:44,437 --> 00:18:47,148
or at my place.
Living together is an option.

329
00:18:48,524 --> 00:18:50,068
You want me to move in with you?

330
00:18:54,656 --> 00:18:56,783
You have a few different options
to consider right now.

331
00:18:56,866 --> 00:18:58,743
You could take out a loan
and move in here,

332
00:18:58,826 --> 00:19:01,663
or look for somewhere else
that fits your budget.

333
00:19:01,746 --> 00:19:05,124
You could even stretch yourself thin
and look into buying your own place.

334
00:19:07,251 --> 00:19:08,461
As another option,

335
00:19:09,087 --> 00:19:10,964
you could also consider marriage.

336
00:19:17,345 --> 00:19:20,139
Wait, is this a proposal, Mr. Kang?

337
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:24,185
I'm ready to do that
at any time, actually.

338
00:19:24,727 --> 00:19:28,439
But today, I'm presenting it
as your housing option number four.

339
00:19:29,816 --> 00:19:31,943
It never once crossed my mind…

340
00:19:33,111 --> 00:19:34,320
that marriage

341
00:19:35,113 --> 00:19:37,657
could be considered as a housing option.

342
00:19:38,908 --> 00:19:42,787
Well, think it over
while you're staying at my place.

343
00:19:48,209 --> 00:19:49,544
What? Do I look pretty?

344
00:19:49,627 --> 00:19:51,421
-You do.
-[laughs]

345
00:19:52,046 --> 00:19:53,589
Like I didn't know that.

346
00:19:54,132 --> 00:19:55,133
[laughs]

347
00:19:56,759 --> 00:19:58,011
[in French] Hello.

348
00:19:58,594 --> 00:20:00,513
Do you speak French?

349
00:20:00,596 --> 00:20:01,806
Yes.

350
00:20:01,889 --> 00:20:03,391
[in English] Come on, help them.

351
00:20:04,892 --> 00:20:05,893
You should try it.

352
00:20:11,983 --> 00:20:14,402
[in French] Uh, can I help you?

353
00:20:14,485 --> 00:20:15,987
Oh, yes. So…

354
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:17,697
[stammers] This place.

355
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:19,407
How do I get there?

356
00:20:20,074 --> 00:20:22,827
Go straight. Uh…

357
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:26,956
At the roundabout. Go 50 meters.

358
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,709
You'll see the sign.

359
00:20:29,792 --> 00:20:31,753
[stammers] I'm sorry,
could you repeat that?

360
00:20:31,836 --> 00:20:33,504
Uh… [chuckles]

361
00:20:34,255 --> 00:20:35,256
Straight.

362
00:20:36,632 --> 00:20:38,384
-Roundabout.
-Mm-hmm.

363
00:20:38,468 --> 00:20:40,219
See the sign.

364
00:20:42,305 --> 00:20:43,723
Okay, I get it.

365
00:20:43,806 --> 00:20:46,642
It was hard
because not many people here speak French.

366
00:20:46,726 --> 00:20:47,769
Thank you so much.

367
00:20:48,394 --> 00:20:50,438
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

368
00:20:50,521 --> 00:20:51,689
-Have a nice trip!
-Thank you.

369
00:20:51,773 --> 00:20:53,441
-Thank you. Have a nice day.
-[No-ah chuckles]

370
00:20:54,984 --> 00:20:55,985
[squeals]

371
00:20:56,069 --> 00:20:58,279
[in English] My French
actually worked! [laughs]

372
00:20:58,362 --> 00:20:59,530
Well done.

373
00:21:00,114 --> 00:21:02,283
Even so, I don't think
they understood at first.

374
00:21:02,366 --> 00:21:04,118
Your pronunciation was a bit shaky,

375
00:21:04,202 --> 00:21:05,953
and you mixed up masculine
with feminine gender.

376
00:21:06,037 --> 00:21:07,497
Did I?

377
00:21:08,331 --> 00:21:09,332
Ugh.

378
00:21:09,415 --> 00:21:12,043
French is so hard because of the genders.

379
00:21:12,126 --> 00:21:15,088
This won't do.
I'll just have to teach you a lot more.

380
00:21:15,171 --> 00:21:16,172
Like what?

381
00:21:17,715 --> 00:21:18,716
Gender differences.

382
00:21:27,475 --> 00:21:28,643
[Jae-in sighs]

383
00:21:51,249 --> 00:21:52,291
FRENCH LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY TEST

384
00:21:56,546 --> 00:21:57,922
So you're really just studying?

385
00:21:58,005 --> 00:21:59,423
Let me quiz you.

386
00:22:00,258 --> 00:22:01,259
Okay.

387
00:22:06,264 --> 00:22:09,142
So, is "beard" masculine or feminine?

388
00:22:09,225 --> 00:22:11,394
Well, it's masculine, of course.

389
00:22:11,477 --> 00:22:13,980
Wrong. It's feminine.

390
00:22:14,063 --> 00:22:15,148
[sighs] Really?

391
00:22:15,731 --> 00:22:16,774
Then,

392
00:22:18,192 --> 00:22:19,443
what about hair?

393
00:22:20,778 --> 00:22:22,071
Hmm…

394
00:22:22,155 --> 00:22:23,781
It's feminine?

395
00:22:23,865 --> 00:22:25,700
No. It's masculine.

396
00:22:25,783 --> 00:22:27,034
[groans]

397
00:22:27,660 --> 00:22:29,996
French is so hard because of the genders.

398
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:32,665
And that's the reason why
you shouldn't try to use logic.

399
00:22:32,748 --> 00:22:33,875
Memorize them.

400
00:22:41,048 --> 00:22:43,259
-And this?
-I know this.

401
00:22:43,843 --> 00:22:46,137
La bise. That's feminine.

402
00:22:47,096 --> 00:22:49,098
What about what you and I are doing?

403
00:22:49,932 --> 00:22:51,976
And what are we doing?

404
00:22:53,394 --> 00:22:54,729
Embrasser.

405
00:22:55,605 --> 00:22:57,398
It's actually a verb, not a noun.

406
00:22:57,481 --> 00:22:59,775
["Ma Belle Additionelle" playing]

407
00:23:52,662 --> 00:23:54,830
FRENCH LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY TEST

408
00:23:54,914 --> 00:23:55,915
[song ends]

409
00:24:05,299 --> 00:24:06,634
You can put your clothes in here.

410
00:24:06,717 --> 00:24:09,637
I see that you have so much empty space.

411
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,472
Too big for one person, huh?

412
00:24:11,555 --> 00:24:14,183
Once you're done unpacking,
I'll make us some tea.

413
00:24:14,267 --> 00:24:15,309
Okay.

414
00:24:28,197 --> 00:24:30,199
[soft music playing]

415
00:24:31,617 --> 00:24:33,869
[Ji-yoon] I received a strange proposal.

416
00:24:35,997 --> 00:24:39,917
A proposal completely different
from the one I had made.

417
00:24:44,046 --> 00:24:46,716
Not something emotional and impulsive,

418
00:24:46,799 --> 00:24:48,843
but a calm and rational offer.

419
00:24:51,053 --> 00:24:54,056
That's right.
This is how marriages should really go.

420
00:25:13,117 --> 00:25:15,202
-[sighs]
-So why…

421
00:25:16,495 --> 00:25:18,164
do I feel this way?

422
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:25,379
I love Mr. Kang so much,
and I don't ever want us to break up.

423
00:25:26,255 --> 00:25:27,757
So why…

424
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,092
So why am I hesitating about it?

425
00:25:40,353 --> 00:25:41,896
Ms. Cha, congratulations.

426
00:25:41,979 --> 00:25:43,647
Why? For what?

427
00:25:43,731 --> 00:25:45,733
You're getting a promotion.

428
00:25:45,816 --> 00:25:48,861
What do you mean?
It's not even promotion season.

429
00:25:48,944 --> 00:25:51,447
It's a special one! [chuckles]

430
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:53,532
[sighs] Manager Cha Ji-yoon,

431
00:25:53,616 --> 00:25:55,743
how on earth are you going
to be able to lead a team

432
00:25:55,826 --> 00:25:58,120
-if you're so slow on the uptake?
-[chuckles]

433
00:25:58,204 --> 00:26:00,289
Mr. Jeon is also a special candidate.

434
00:26:00,373 --> 00:26:01,749
Really?

435
00:26:01,832 --> 00:26:05,711
Finally! I'm finally making
senior associate. [chuckles]

436
00:26:05,795 --> 00:26:07,588
President Han recommended you both,

437
00:26:07,671 --> 00:26:10,800
and Mr. Kang even sent
your performance reports to HR.

438
00:26:11,717 --> 00:26:15,388
I'm so jealous.
I should've applied to the task force too.

439
00:26:15,971 --> 00:26:18,307
Well, it's not like everyone
who applies makes it, though.

440
00:26:18,391 --> 00:26:19,725
[sighs]

441
00:26:19,809 --> 00:26:22,311
And even if you did,
it doesn't mean you'll get a promotion.

442
00:26:22,395 --> 00:26:24,939
Come on, I'm sure you're up next.

443
00:26:25,022 --> 00:26:27,608
You're great at marketing.
I bet you'll get it after the launch.

444
00:26:27,691 --> 00:26:29,652
Oh, uh, thank you.

445
00:26:31,278 --> 00:26:34,198
Excuse me, folks, I'd appreciate it
if you'd focus on me for a sec.

446
00:26:34,281 --> 00:26:35,825
It's only a recommendation.

447
00:26:35,908 --> 00:26:38,869
Who knows what will happen
once HR starts the vetting process?

448
00:26:38,953 --> 00:26:40,371
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

449
00:26:40,454 --> 00:26:41,705
Too late.

450
00:26:41,789 --> 00:26:43,749
I've already bragged to my wife about it.

451
00:26:43,833 --> 00:26:47,253
-Don't… Don't you dare jinx me, all right?
-[chuckles]

452
00:26:49,130 --> 00:26:51,757
-[footsteps approaching]
-[Young-sam clears throat]

453
00:26:51,841 --> 00:26:53,384
You better not. [chuckles]

454
00:27:14,405 --> 00:27:16,532
[upbeat music playing]

455
00:27:20,786 --> 00:27:21,787
[mouthing] Yes!

456
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:30,421
[sighs]

457
00:27:30,921 --> 00:27:31,922
[phone buzzes]

458
00:27:38,345 --> 00:27:41,307
[Si-woo] Don't let your guard down
until the final results are announced.

459
00:27:42,016 --> 00:27:43,517
But still, congratulations.

460
00:27:47,521 --> 00:27:48,647
[Ji-yoon] Hang on.

461
00:27:49,356 --> 00:27:51,650
If I want to keep climbing
the corporate ladder,

462
00:27:51,734 --> 00:27:53,944
wouldn't it be better not to get married?

463
00:27:56,947 --> 00:27:58,699
-Ms. Cha.
-Yes?

464
00:27:58,782 --> 00:28:00,242
Mr. Jeon wants us to join him.

465
00:28:01,035 --> 00:28:02,369
Oh. I'll be right there.

466
00:28:05,206 --> 00:28:06,373
[sighs]

467
00:28:10,336 --> 00:28:11,337
[sighs]

468
00:28:11,420 --> 00:28:14,673
[Ji-yoon] Oh, right.
President Han is married too, huh?

469
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:23,307
As for the Home-AI Zone,

470
00:28:24,141 --> 00:28:25,142
we won't do it.

471
00:28:25,226 --> 00:28:26,685
-Sorry?
-Pardon?

472
00:28:26,769 --> 00:28:29,063
We concluded that it would create
an uneven playing field

473
00:28:29,146 --> 00:28:30,147
for other companies.

474
00:28:30,689 --> 00:28:32,399
-[sighs]
-I'm sorry.

475
00:28:32,483 --> 00:28:34,860
Well, uh, do you think maybe you could

476
00:28:35,486 --> 00:28:37,821
reconsider, perhaps? [chuckles] Uh.

477
00:28:37,905 --> 00:28:39,240
We understand.

478
00:28:39,740 --> 00:28:42,409
We'll follow up with
a more viable proposal for your store.

479
00:28:42,493 --> 00:28:43,452
Sure.

480
00:28:48,958 --> 00:28:51,085
-[sighs] This isn't easy.
-[sighs]

481
00:28:51,168 --> 00:28:53,212
If they accepted our proposal,

482
00:28:53,712 --> 00:28:56,382
it's obvious that our competitors
would be pushing back.

483
00:28:56,465 --> 00:28:58,300
[customer] Look, honey,
investing in premium appliances

484
00:28:58,384 --> 00:29:00,594
from the start is the way
to save money in the long run!

485
00:29:00,678 --> 00:29:03,556
Let's wait until we move into
a bigger place and buy them then.

486
00:29:03,639 --> 00:29:04,932
And when is that gonna be?

487
00:29:05,015 --> 00:29:06,433
Forget it, I'm not marrying you.

488
00:29:07,184 --> 00:29:09,728
That again?
So when are you going to marry me?

489
00:29:10,312 --> 00:29:11,313
[groans]

490
00:29:12,273 --> 00:29:13,983
-Where are you going?
-Classic.

491
00:29:14,066 --> 00:29:16,235
Every marriage
always kicks off with a fight.

492
00:29:16,318 --> 00:29:17,486
[sighs]

493
00:29:18,195 --> 00:29:19,530
Do you really fight that much?

494
00:29:24,159 --> 00:29:26,662
We fought over wanting
to watch different TV shows,

495
00:29:26,745 --> 00:29:29,873
mmm, over eating out
versus cooking at home,

496
00:29:30,374 --> 00:29:32,167
and over treating
our families differently.

497
00:29:32,251 --> 00:29:34,336
We fought so much
when we were newlyweds. Ugh!

498
00:29:34,420 --> 00:29:36,547
Then how do you make it work?

499
00:29:37,798 --> 00:29:39,883
It's like riding an invisible seesaw.

500
00:29:39,967 --> 00:29:42,386
Since I got my way on this,
I concede on that.

501
00:29:42,469 --> 00:29:45,264
Since you let it slide last time,
I'll look away this time.

502
00:29:45,347 --> 00:29:48,017
Rocking back and forth like that.
That's how you strike a balance.

503
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:50,853
[groans] Sounds exhausting
just hearing about it.

504
00:29:50,936 --> 00:29:52,146
But, you know,

505
00:29:52,688 --> 00:29:54,398
you eventually get the hang of it.

506
00:29:54,481 --> 00:29:56,900
Yeah. When things feel tense,
you run and do some chores.

507
00:29:56,984 --> 00:29:58,611
What if the seesaw tips too far?

508
00:29:58,694 --> 00:29:59,862
Then it all explodes.

509
00:30:00,446 --> 00:30:02,990
Fights between husband and wife
are inevitable.

510
00:30:03,073 --> 00:30:05,326
What matters is how you make up after.

511
00:30:05,409 --> 00:30:06,869
And how do you two make up?

512
00:30:06,952 --> 00:30:09,538
We, uh, agree to keep our mouths shut

513
00:30:09,622 --> 00:30:11,498
but to stay within view of each other.

514
00:30:11,582 --> 00:30:12,625
-[sighs]
-The thing is,

515
00:30:12,708 --> 00:30:14,543
neither of us are allowed to walk away.

516
00:30:15,210 --> 00:30:17,588
-[chuckles]
-[sighs] Marriage is hard work.

517
00:30:18,088 --> 00:30:21,050
Why? Mr. Kang ask you
to marry him? [laughing]

518
00:30:23,135 --> 00:30:25,012
I need to hit the restroom.
My stomach hurts.

519
00:30:25,095 --> 00:30:26,096
Be right back.

520
00:30:28,265 --> 00:30:29,475
What did you just say now?

521
00:30:30,059 --> 00:30:31,727
I said I'm going to the restroom.

522
00:30:31,810 --> 00:30:32,936
Hey, Jeon Kee-tae.

523
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:34,229
Stop right there!

524
00:30:34,730 --> 00:30:35,731
Hey!

525
00:30:44,156 --> 00:30:46,033
I must've let my guard down.

526
00:30:46,116 --> 00:30:48,577
Turns out Kee-tae already knows about us.

527
00:30:48,661 --> 00:30:50,037
And the rumors haven't spread yet?

528
00:30:50,788 --> 00:30:52,748
Thankfully, he hasn't told anyone.

529
00:30:52,831 --> 00:30:54,667
And he said he never will.

530
00:30:55,584 --> 00:30:57,670
Looks like Mr. Jeon's quite loyal.

531
00:31:02,508 --> 00:31:04,760
By the way,
why do you keep your tea so far away?

532
00:31:04,843 --> 00:31:08,555
If you just left them there,
it'd be easier to find and make a cup.

533
00:31:08,639 --> 00:31:11,433
Oh. I just don't like
having things lying around.

534
00:31:11,517 --> 00:31:12,685
Oh.

535
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:15,688
I need these to be in my view.
I'll put them back.

536
00:31:16,397 --> 00:31:17,398
No.

537
00:31:17,981 --> 00:31:20,150
Leave them here. Whatever works for you.

538
00:31:30,869 --> 00:31:33,288
I guess you sleep well
only when it's completely dark.

539
00:31:33,372 --> 00:31:35,666
Yes. It's not the case for you?

540
00:31:35,749 --> 00:31:39,169
To be honest,
I can't sleep very well if it's too dark.

541
00:31:39,253 --> 00:31:40,546
-[chuckles]
-Oh.

542
00:31:41,422 --> 00:31:42,965
You should've told me sooner.

543
00:31:50,139 --> 00:31:51,140
Mr. Kang,

544
00:31:51,765 --> 00:31:53,684
are you always going to
change your ways for me?

545
00:31:54,601 --> 00:31:56,854
-Of course I am.
-But for how long?

546
00:31:58,063 --> 00:32:01,108
It's fine for now,
but you can't do that forever.

547
00:32:02,401 --> 00:32:03,694
Would that be too hard?

548
00:32:03,777 --> 00:32:07,322
Someone told me that marriage
is like riding a seesaw.

549
00:32:07,906 --> 00:32:09,575
One person gives in this time,

550
00:32:09,658 --> 00:32:11,910
and the other person
gives in the next time.

551
00:32:11,994 --> 00:32:13,746
If only one side keeps giving in,

552
00:32:13,829 --> 00:32:15,914
one day the seesaw won't move anymore.

553
00:32:18,959 --> 00:32:21,462
All right, so let's find a way
that works for us.

554
00:32:27,217 --> 00:32:32,681
[Ji-yoon] Will I ever be able to set aside
everything about myself for him too?

555
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:35,851
[phone buzzing]

556
00:32:35,934 --> 00:32:40,856
6:00 A.M.
WAKE UP

557
00:32:47,905 --> 00:32:49,364
[sighs]

558
00:34:12,948 --> 00:34:14,950
[Si-woo humming]

559
00:34:22,332 --> 00:34:24,209
[humming continues]

560
00:34:26,795 --> 00:34:28,547
[humming stops]

561
00:34:30,048 --> 00:34:32,259
[resumes humming]

562
00:34:48,233 --> 00:34:50,485
[humming continues]

563
00:35:01,830 --> 00:35:03,624
These moments feel like a gift,

564
00:35:03,707 --> 00:35:06,168
which I never would've known
by living alone.

565
00:35:07,127 --> 00:35:08,128
Did you sleep well?

566
00:35:09,922 --> 00:35:11,006
Should've woken me up.

567
00:35:11,089 --> 00:35:13,508
That way, I could've heard
more of your singing.

568
00:35:15,802 --> 00:35:17,638
You'll hear plenty of it in the future.

569
00:35:22,309 --> 00:35:23,602
I'm ready.

570
00:35:23,685 --> 00:35:25,145
Let's go, Mr. Kang.

571
00:35:28,649 --> 00:35:30,734
You're already incredibly beautiful, but…

572
00:35:34,655 --> 00:35:35,656
[chuckles]

573
00:35:42,204 --> 00:35:47,542
SI-WOO'S - JI-YOON'S

574
00:35:47,626 --> 00:35:48,710
I know. Come on.

575
00:35:48,794 --> 00:35:52,297
It's ridiculous that Ms. Cha
is going to hold the same rank as us!

576
00:35:52,381 --> 00:35:55,842
We need to take collective action to block
this kind of reckless fast-tracking.

577
00:35:55,926 --> 00:35:57,344
We can't sit back and watch.

578
00:35:57,928 --> 00:36:01,223
Exactly. If she were under me,
I would've given the worst review.

579
00:36:02,683 --> 00:36:05,811
[coworker 1] Did you all see
the Global Talent Development Program?

580
00:36:05,894 --> 00:36:08,939
[Young-sam in distance] Right?
Yes. Duh, that's right.

581
00:36:09,731 --> 00:36:10,607
GLOBAL TALENT
DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM

582
00:36:12,943 --> 00:36:14,653
[coworker 2] What's the point of looking?

583
00:36:14,736 --> 00:36:17,072
Married guys like me
can't go anywhere anyway.

584
00:36:17,155 --> 00:36:19,282
[coworker 3] I'd even bolt right now
because of our boss,

585
00:36:19,366 --> 00:36:21,618
but I don't meet the requirements.
[chuckles]

586
00:36:25,288 --> 00:36:27,499
ASSIGNMENT COUNTRIES:
RUSSIA, DUBAI, SENEGAL, VIETNAM

587
00:36:29,918 --> 00:36:32,754
[coworker 1] They pay your full salary
and all your living expenses?

588
00:36:32,838 --> 00:36:34,089
What a sweet deal.

589
00:36:36,842 --> 00:36:38,802
[coworker 3] You need
at least three years' experience

590
00:36:38,885 --> 00:36:41,596
with good performance reviews,
Mr. First-year.

591
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:43,932
REGIONAL SPECIALIST RECRUITMENT

592
00:36:44,808 --> 00:36:46,810
A regional specialist?

593
00:36:49,187 --> 00:36:50,230
Okay, got it.

594
00:36:53,275 --> 00:36:55,235
Wait, aren't you all supposed to be
in the design meeting?

595
00:36:55,819 --> 00:36:58,488
Oh. But the meeting's next week.

596
00:36:58,572 --> 00:37:01,199
The Design Team
is at an exhibition until today, sir.

597
00:37:01,283 --> 00:37:04,411
How many times do I have to tell you
to give me a heads-up on stuff like that?!

598
00:37:04,911 --> 00:37:06,288
-[groans]
-But I did tell you.

599
00:37:06,371 --> 00:37:07,956
Geez.

600
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:09,458
[sighs] Goodness.

601
00:37:11,001 --> 00:37:12,753
Goddamn it!

602
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:14,921
Ugh!

603
00:37:15,547 --> 00:37:16,673
[sighs]

604
00:37:17,674 --> 00:37:18,759
[sighs]

605
00:37:25,515 --> 00:37:26,767
[sighs]

606
00:37:26,850 --> 00:37:29,186
How much longer
do I have to put up with Mr. Ko?

607
00:37:29,269 --> 00:37:30,937
Just wait a little while.

608
00:37:31,021 --> 00:37:32,689
You delivered results this time,

609
00:37:32,773 --> 00:37:34,983
so you should be able to transfer
to any team you want.

610
00:37:35,067 --> 00:37:36,068
[sighs]

611
00:37:37,277 --> 00:37:39,821
Ji-Yoon, have you ever been to Senegal?

612
00:37:40,781 --> 00:37:43,992
Are you talking about
the Global Talent Development Program?

613
00:37:44,076 --> 00:37:45,952
[chuckles] Yes.

614
00:37:46,036 --> 00:37:49,831
I saw that Senegal was on the list,
and I just can't stop thinking about it.

615
00:37:49,915 --> 00:37:51,249
It'd be great if you went.

616
00:37:51,333 --> 00:37:53,335
Most people are scared to take the leap,

617
00:37:53,418 --> 00:37:56,463
but you'll definitely level up
if you decide to go.

618
00:37:56,546 --> 00:37:58,006
And it sets you up as an expat.

619
00:37:59,007 --> 00:38:02,511
I'm scared, though. It's not like everyone
who applies gets accepted.

620
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,555
Have you never thought about it before?

621
00:38:06,598 --> 00:38:10,143
I probably would have considered it
if I were still stuck under Mr. Ko,

622
00:38:10,644 --> 00:38:11,686
but I can't go now.

623
00:38:11,770 --> 00:38:13,647
Because of Mr. Kang?

624
00:38:14,231 --> 00:38:18,110
Mmm. I don't really want
to leave him alone like that. [chuckles]

625
00:38:18,193 --> 00:38:19,361
[scoffs]

626
00:38:20,278 --> 00:38:23,365
[sighs] At this rate, you'll be saying
you're marrying him next.

627
00:38:24,074 --> 00:38:25,200
I used to think

628
00:38:26,118 --> 00:38:28,620
that marriage was the natural
next step after dating.

629
00:38:29,871 --> 00:38:33,333
That as long as you loved each other,
then that was really enough.

630
00:38:34,084 --> 00:38:36,461
But not anymore.
There's so much to consider.

631
00:38:37,045 --> 00:38:38,296
And what are you considering, huh?

632
00:38:38,380 --> 00:38:41,675
Whether marriage
will be getting in the way of my career,

633
00:38:41,758 --> 00:38:44,553
whether I can truly live well
with this person,

634
00:38:45,053 --> 00:38:46,555
and most of all,

635
00:38:46,638 --> 00:38:50,142
whether I'm certain
that we will never break up.

636
00:38:51,268 --> 00:38:52,686
Why are you being so intense?

637
00:38:52,769 --> 00:38:54,688
People get married
and divorced all the time.

638
00:38:54,771 --> 00:38:55,981
[sighs]

639
00:38:57,357 --> 00:38:58,608
I can't do that.

640
00:39:00,193 --> 00:39:01,987
[Ji-yoon] I can't let him

641
00:39:02,070 --> 00:39:05,115
experience failure twice.

642
00:39:05,198 --> 00:39:06,491
[coughs]

643
00:39:09,035 --> 00:39:10,036
You're living together?

644
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:12,330
I believe I clearly said it's temporary.

645
00:39:12,414 --> 00:39:14,624
Whether it's temporary or just for a day…

646
00:39:14,708 --> 00:39:18,170
Well, have you lived with another person
in the last ten years?

647
00:39:18,253 --> 00:39:19,504
I haven't.

648
00:39:19,588 --> 00:39:22,048
So is it okay?
Especially for a picky guy like you?

649
00:39:22,132 --> 00:39:24,176
At first, I was quite concerned too.

650
00:39:24,259 --> 00:39:26,344
"Will I be able to live
with another person again?"

651
00:39:27,179 --> 00:39:29,598
But, you know,
it's not as bad as I thought.

652
00:39:29,681 --> 00:39:31,558
Actually, I love it. A lot.

653
00:39:31,641 --> 00:39:32,726
Wow.

654
00:39:33,310 --> 00:39:37,189
I guess love truly is the only thing
that can change a person.

655
00:39:37,272 --> 00:39:38,356
[both chuckle]

656
00:39:44,404 --> 00:39:47,282
Anyway, how could you
possibly propose to her

657
00:39:47,365 --> 00:39:49,868
by giving her marriage
as another housing option?

658
00:39:49,951 --> 00:39:52,579
You should buy flowers and a ring
and do it properly.

659
00:39:52,662 --> 00:39:55,123
Then it would become hard
for her to say no.

660
00:39:55,207 --> 00:39:57,375
I didn't want to make her feel pressured.

661
00:39:57,459 --> 00:40:01,046
[sighs] But don't you think
she still felt a bit disappointed?

662
00:40:02,214 --> 00:40:05,050
She might even be wondering
if you were being serious.

663
00:40:09,512 --> 00:40:11,514
[playful music playing]

664
00:40:19,314 --> 00:40:20,440
[clears throat]

665
00:40:23,276 --> 00:40:24,861
[giggles]

666
00:40:28,490 --> 00:40:29,491
Hmm…

667
00:40:33,286 --> 00:40:34,621
Why do you keep following me?

668
00:40:35,330 --> 00:40:37,374
-Because you're beautiful.
-[chuckles]

669
00:40:37,457 --> 00:40:39,834
If you're just doing this
because of my beauty,

670
00:40:39,918 --> 00:40:40,919
then I'll pass.

671
00:40:41,002 --> 00:40:44,464
You see, I'm looking for a man
who can appreciate my inner beauty.

672
00:40:44,547 --> 00:40:46,049
Therefore, just give it up, please.

673
00:40:46,883 --> 00:40:48,093
You've got me all wrong.

674
00:40:48,176 --> 00:40:50,053
All I've been seeing is your inner beauty.

675
00:40:53,556 --> 00:40:55,100
Is that another wrong answer?

676
00:40:55,183 --> 00:40:56,226
Yes.

677
00:40:56,309 --> 00:41:00,897
You need to start thinking
outside the box, you know? [chuckles]

678
00:41:12,826 --> 00:41:14,244
Then how about this?

679
00:41:15,787 --> 00:41:17,372
Wait, what is this?

680
00:41:17,455 --> 00:41:20,750
My feelings for you.
Not too heavy, but definitely not shallow.

681
00:41:23,753 --> 00:41:25,922
You don't have to feel bad
about saying no.

682
00:41:26,006 --> 00:41:30,260
I really want you to seriously think
about what's best for you.

683
00:41:32,512 --> 00:41:34,222
I guess I like rings.

684
00:41:34,806 --> 00:41:37,892
Almost forgot all I've been
contemplating over until now.

685
00:41:39,102 --> 00:41:41,896
Contemplate a little more
until you finish that.

686
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:43,857
I'm going to really savor it.

687
00:41:43,940 --> 00:41:45,358
[chuckles]

688
00:41:47,193 --> 00:41:49,571
[gasps] This thing is huge, isn't it?

689
00:41:49,654 --> 00:41:51,156
[chuckling]

690
00:42:00,206 --> 00:42:01,207
[Young-sam] Mr. Noh,

691
00:42:01,291 --> 00:42:02,876
could we at least grab dinner?

692
00:42:02,959 --> 00:42:06,212
Please give me one more chance.
I'll make sure to deliver this time.

693
00:42:07,172 --> 00:42:08,173
Mr. Noh!

694
00:42:08,256 --> 00:42:11,009
I have discovered
some shocking news to share with you!

695
00:42:12,010 --> 00:42:14,471
MANAGING DIRECTOR NOH

696
00:42:15,347 --> 00:42:17,515
[sobbing]

697
00:42:17,599 --> 00:42:18,850
Damn. Damn it!

698
00:42:22,228 --> 00:42:23,563
[sighs]

699
00:42:25,565 --> 00:42:27,400
[scoffs, breathes heavily]

700
00:42:27,484 --> 00:42:29,611
You always ride
on other people's coattails,

701
00:42:29,694 --> 00:42:31,404
and now you're just handing it over
to Ms. Cha?

702
00:42:31,488 --> 00:42:33,656
Why? To screw me over?

703
00:42:34,616 --> 00:42:37,285
Are you so afraid that
I'll make Managing Director before you?

704
00:42:37,369 --> 00:42:39,746
I'm not afraid
of incompetent people at all,

705
00:42:39,829 --> 00:42:41,289
or those who play dirty.

706
00:42:41,373 --> 00:42:42,540
[sighs]

707
00:42:43,249 --> 00:42:44,834
You still haven't come to your senses.

708
00:42:44,918 --> 00:42:47,087
You're the one
who hasn't come to your senses.

709
00:42:47,837 --> 00:42:50,048
Are you sure that lifeline of yours

710
00:42:50,131 --> 00:42:51,633
is even a reliable one?

711
00:42:52,842 --> 00:42:55,470
At this rate, you might
end up reporting to Ms. Cha.

712
00:42:55,553 --> 00:42:56,805
You… You bastard!

713
00:42:57,514 --> 00:42:59,933
I know I may not be able to pull you up,

714
00:43:00,016 --> 00:43:02,560
but I can sure drag you
straight to the bottom!

715
00:43:02,644 --> 00:43:04,145
[breathing shakily]

716
00:43:05,313 --> 00:43:07,148
[rock music plays]

717
00:43:07,232 --> 00:43:09,651
[grunting]

718
00:43:12,862 --> 00:43:13,863
I can't wait.

719
00:43:18,618 --> 00:43:19,953
[sighs] Damn it.

720
00:43:20,036 --> 00:43:22,747
[breathing heavily]

721
00:43:25,083 --> 00:43:26,751
Geez. Gosh…

722
00:43:28,169 --> 00:43:29,170
[employee 1] Thank you.

723
00:43:29,254 --> 00:43:30,839
[employee 2] Good luck
with the wedding planning.

724
00:43:30,922 --> 00:43:32,715
[sighs] I'll get going now.

725
00:43:32,799 --> 00:43:34,342
[Na-ri] I heard
she's getting married next month,

726
00:43:34,426 --> 00:43:36,469
and she's already
transferring departments?

727
00:43:36,553 --> 00:43:38,096
-See you.
-Bye. Stay in touch.

728
00:43:38,179 --> 00:43:39,347
I will.

729
00:43:39,431 --> 00:43:40,932
-I forgot about that.
-[employee 3] Goodbye.

730
00:43:41,015 --> 00:43:42,767
-[employee 2] Take care.
-About what?

731
00:43:42,851 --> 00:43:46,312
That married couples aren't allowed
to work in the same department.

732
00:43:46,396 --> 00:43:48,731
It's not that they can't,
they choose not to.

733
00:43:48,815 --> 00:43:50,483
It'd be so awkward to work together.

734
00:43:51,067 --> 00:43:52,152
You think so?

735
00:43:54,988 --> 00:43:58,825
But that means one of them might be forced
to give up the work they love.

736
00:43:58,908 --> 00:44:00,118
That's true.

737
00:44:00,201 --> 00:44:01,786
And let's face it,

738
00:44:01,870 --> 00:44:04,080
it's usually the one who's more junior.

739
00:44:04,664 --> 00:44:08,042
[scoffs] Yeah, office marriages
are a terrible idea.

740
00:44:12,714 --> 00:44:14,674
Double-check that
before you show me, okay?

741
00:44:14,757 --> 00:44:15,967
Okay.

742
00:44:16,050 --> 00:44:17,051
Great work.

743
00:44:21,973 --> 00:44:22,974
[sighs]

744
00:44:34,444 --> 00:44:36,404
-Uh, Ms. Choi?
-Yes?

745
00:44:47,165 --> 00:44:49,250
Ms. Choi, we'll get the proposal copied.

746
00:44:49,334 --> 00:44:51,377
-[Soo-jin] That was good enough.
-Thank you, ma'am.

747
00:44:52,295 --> 00:44:53,671
Ji-yoon.

748
00:44:54,464 --> 00:44:55,632
Ms. Choi.

749
00:44:59,052 --> 00:45:00,345
I already heard.

750
00:45:04,140 --> 00:45:05,433
Thank you.

751
00:45:08,394 --> 00:45:09,395
See you.

752
00:45:15,193 --> 00:45:16,319
[sighs]

753
00:45:21,115 --> 00:45:23,034
-A themed zone?
-Yes.

754
00:45:23,117 --> 00:45:25,620
Instead of just building our Home-AI Zone,

755
00:45:25,703 --> 00:45:28,831
we propose letting our competitors set up
their own themed zones as well.

756
00:45:28,915 --> 00:45:30,792
Is it really necessary to go that far?

757
00:45:30,875 --> 00:45:33,461
Well, if it means we can set up
our Home-AI Zone,

758
00:45:33,545 --> 00:45:34,796
then why not?

759
00:45:34,879 --> 00:45:36,005
It would be to our benefit.

760
00:45:36,089 --> 00:45:38,174
And what's your reasoning behind that?

761
00:45:38,258 --> 00:45:39,551
Given the current market,

762
00:45:39,634 --> 00:45:42,845
I believe running ahead on our own
won't win us any applause.

763
00:45:42,929 --> 00:45:46,057
We need to let our partners
and competitors grow with us.

764
00:45:46,140 --> 00:45:49,227
In fact, we just need
to stay half a step ahead.

765
00:45:49,310 --> 00:45:52,772
Frankly, I'm sure we'll win regardless
of what themed zone they bring in.

766
00:45:52,855 --> 00:45:55,275
[chuckles] I knew it.

767
00:45:56,359 --> 00:45:58,778
-I wasn't wrong about you.
-What?

768
00:45:58,861 --> 00:46:01,948
Chasing you down to get you on this team
was totally worth it.

769
00:46:04,742 --> 00:46:06,494
[inhales sharply] You see,

770
00:46:07,245 --> 00:46:11,040
if we got married,
I would have to go to another department.

771
00:46:11,124 --> 00:46:13,585
-Says who?
-Company policy.

772
00:46:13,668 --> 00:46:15,670
Married couples can't work
in the same department.

773
00:46:15,753 --> 00:46:18,673
Exactly, so why should you be
the one to move?

774
00:46:19,173 --> 00:46:20,800
If anyone's moving, it'll be me.

775
00:46:25,346 --> 00:46:26,514
Mr. Kang,

776
00:46:27,098 --> 00:46:28,808
I'm going back to my place.

777
00:46:31,102 --> 00:46:32,270
Why?

778
00:46:32,353 --> 00:46:35,440
Well, the police called me this afternoon.
They caught the burglar.

779
00:46:36,941 --> 00:46:39,277
Ah. That's a relief.

780
00:46:40,028 --> 00:46:43,239
[sighs] But I'm still a little scared,

781
00:46:43,323 --> 00:46:45,116
so could you stay with me tonight?

782
00:46:46,909 --> 00:46:48,036
Of course.

783
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:53,499
So are you done contemplating?

784
00:46:54,667 --> 00:46:55,668
Yes.

785
00:46:57,337 --> 00:46:58,630
And did you find your answer?

786
00:46:59,672 --> 00:47:00,673
Yes.

787
00:47:01,674 --> 00:47:04,510
In regards to the fourth housing option…

788
00:47:05,762 --> 00:47:07,930
[keypad beeping]

789
00:47:09,891 --> 00:47:11,267
Huh?

790
00:47:12,727 --> 00:47:14,312
A… A burglar?

791
00:47:19,859 --> 00:47:21,569
[keypad beeping]

792
00:47:21,653 --> 00:47:22,779
Stay here.

793
00:47:34,791 --> 00:47:35,792
No way.

794
00:47:36,417 --> 00:47:37,710
Why aren't you going in?

795
00:47:38,878 --> 00:47:41,547
[high-pitched ringing]

796
00:47:44,342 --> 00:47:46,594
[tense music playing]

797
00:47:49,097 --> 00:47:50,098
Dad.

798
00:47:53,059 --> 00:47:55,687
Dad, please sit down first.
Let's sit down and--

799
00:47:55,770 --> 00:47:57,855
Your daughter and I are dating, sir.

800
00:47:59,023 --> 00:48:00,149
You…

801
00:48:00,775 --> 00:48:02,068
Dad, I'm sorry.

802
00:48:02,151 --> 00:48:03,528
I should've told you sooner.

803
00:48:06,614 --> 00:48:07,615
Outside.

804
00:48:15,915 --> 00:48:17,041
Wait, Dad.

805
00:48:17,625 --> 00:48:19,877
Stay here. I'll be right back.

806
00:48:26,342 --> 00:48:29,637
[sighs] Why didn't you tell me
that you were coming over?

807
00:48:29,721 --> 00:48:31,139
I did.

808
00:48:31,222 --> 00:48:33,266
I called, but you didn't answer.

809
00:48:36,561 --> 00:48:39,480
We thought you weren't home,
so we were gonna leave the kimchi and go.

810
00:48:39,564 --> 00:48:40,982
[sighs]

811
00:48:41,065 --> 00:48:43,985
That guy. He's from the kiss cam, right?

812
00:48:44,694 --> 00:48:45,695
[groans]

813
00:48:45,778 --> 00:48:49,198
-How come Dad already knows him?
-For starters, don't say a word to Mom.

814
00:48:57,457 --> 00:48:58,750
[sighs]

815
00:48:58,833 --> 00:49:00,626
You should pace yourself.

816
00:49:01,419 --> 00:49:03,004
When did you two start dating?

817
00:49:03,087 --> 00:49:06,424
We met in the summer
and then started dating in the fall.

818
00:49:07,133 --> 00:49:08,801
And now it's a snowy winter.

819
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:12,555
You're telling me
you lied this whole time.

820
00:49:13,097 --> 00:49:14,307
I'm sorry, sir.

821
00:49:16,559 --> 00:49:17,685
Come to think of it,

822
00:49:19,020 --> 00:49:21,397
I've never asked you
what company you worked for anyway.

823
00:49:22,190 --> 00:49:23,941
That's exactly why I liked you, sir.

824
00:49:24,442 --> 00:49:27,737
You never asked what I did,
what school I went to,

825
00:49:27,820 --> 00:49:29,197
or how much money I made.

826
00:49:29,781 --> 00:49:31,616
You didn't ask any of those things.

827
00:49:32,533 --> 00:49:33,826
You just

828
00:49:34,911 --> 00:49:36,537
saw me for who I was.

829
00:49:38,873 --> 00:49:40,458
Well, I'm regretting it now.

830
00:49:43,544 --> 00:49:45,213
Let me ask you this straight up.

831
00:49:48,049 --> 00:49:49,759
Are you dating my Ji-yoon

832
00:49:50,718 --> 00:49:52,929
with the intention
of getting married to her?

833
00:49:53,429 --> 00:49:56,057
You're going to get angry
no matter how I answer that.

834
00:49:56,140 --> 00:49:57,308
You're damn right.

835
00:49:57,975 --> 00:49:58,976
I am angry, kid.

836
00:50:02,104 --> 00:50:03,356
You're laughing, punk?

837
00:50:09,028 --> 00:50:10,988
See, I know what you're worried about

838
00:50:11,572 --> 00:50:12,782
better than anyone else.

839
00:50:12,865 --> 00:50:14,325
[gentle music playing]

840
00:50:14,408 --> 00:50:15,952
But I want you to know this.

841
00:50:18,329 --> 00:50:22,083
Mr. Cha, I care very deeply about Ji-yoon.

842
00:50:33,803 --> 00:50:34,804
Fine.

843
00:50:36,681 --> 00:50:38,432
It's not like you two are children.

844
00:50:39,475 --> 00:50:41,561
You're both smart enough,
so you'll figure it out.

845
00:50:42,770 --> 00:50:43,855
But still,

846
00:50:45,356 --> 00:50:47,149
I'm against it for now.

847
00:50:48,693 --> 00:50:50,403
And I don't care if that upsets you.

848
00:50:57,702 --> 00:50:58,703
Okay.

849
00:51:08,921 --> 00:51:10,423
[sighs]

850
00:51:10,506 --> 00:51:11,632
Hey, punk,

851
00:51:12,884 --> 00:51:14,427
why did it have to be my Ji-yoon?

852
00:51:20,516 --> 00:51:21,642
[sighs]

853
00:51:29,191 --> 00:51:30,818
-I'm home.
-Oh my.

854
00:51:30,902 --> 00:51:32,612
Oh, my goodness. What is going on?

855
00:51:32,695 --> 00:51:35,573
-Oh, gosh.
-Listen, I always side with my wife.

856
00:51:35,656 --> 00:51:38,242
-[grunts]
-If she says yes, then it's a yes.

857
00:51:38,326 --> 00:51:40,036
And if she says no, it's a no.

858
00:51:40,119 --> 00:51:41,871
-Gosh.
-You got that?!

859
00:51:41,954 --> 00:51:43,915
Why are you acting so strange?

860
00:51:43,998 --> 00:51:45,958
-Where should I set him down?
-[Hye-gyeong] Here. Right here.

861
00:51:46,042 --> 00:51:48,836
Yes. Over here.
Lie down for now. Lie down here.

862
00:51:50,379 --> 00:51:52,298
-Geez.
-[grunts]

863
00:51:52,381 --> 00:51:54,342
[sighs] Thank you.

864
00:51:54,926 --> 00:51:58,012
He barely drinks. I don't understand
what made him drink so much.

865
00:51:59,513 --> 00:52:00,765
And who are you?

866
00:52:00,848 --> 00:52:03,184
Uh, my name is Kang Si-woo, ma'am.

867
00:52:03,267 --> 00:52:05,394
Oh my, aren't you…

868
00:52:06,479 --> 00:52:08,940
very handsome. [chuckles]

869
00:52:10,024 --> 00:52:12,193
But, anyway, how do you know my husband?

870
00:52:13,110 --> 00:52:14,445
I'm a regular at his store.

871
00:52:15,863 --> 00:52:18,240
And what does our Mr. Regular do?

872
00:52:19,200 --> 00:52:20,868
I work at the company SAEUM.

873
00:52:20,952 --> 00:52:22,912
Oh! Oh my!

874
00:52:23,704 --> 00:52:26,123
[stammers] My daughter works there too.

875
00:52:26,207 --> 00:52:29,335
-Her name is Cha Ji-yoon. Oh.
-Mom, I'm home.

876
00:52:30,753 --> 00:52:32,213
Huh?

877
00:52:32,964 --> 00:52:36,759
Wh-What a surprise to see a…
a stranger here.

878
00:52:37,301 --> 00:52:38,302
[chuckles]

879
00:52:39,428 --> 00:52:41,263
I should probably get going now.

880
00:52:41,931 --> 00:52:44,433
At least stay for a cup of tea, please.

881
00:52:47,853 --> 00:52:50,272
[chuckles] That's all right.

882
00:52:50,356 --> 00:52:52,692
I'll introduce myself properly next time.

883
00:52:52,775 --> 00:52:53,943
Bye, Madam.

884
00:52:54,443 --> 00:52:56,278
[romantic music playing]

885
00:52:56,862 --> 00:52:57,863
All right.

886
00:52:57,947 --> 00:53:01,492
Then, I hope we definitely
meet again next time.

887
00:53:18,300 --> 00:53:20,928
My gosh. He called me "Madam."

888
00:53:21,012 --> 00:53:22,138
You heard that, right?

889
00:53:22,722 --> 00:53:25,641
Yes. But I call all the older ladies
"Madam" too.

890
00:53:25,725 --> 00:53:27,101
My goodness.

891
00:53:27,601 --> 00:53:30,396
He's polite and treats elders so well.

892
00:53:31,522 --> 00:53:34,066
I wonder if he's married. [chuckling]

893
00:53:37,236 --> 00:53:38,779
[sighs]

894
00:53:48,247 --> 00:53:50,624
[sighs] My dad gave you an earful,
didn't he?

895
00:53:50,708 --> 00:53:54,462
He bought me drinks, gave me advice,
and put his arms around my shoulder.

896
00:53:54,545 --> 00:53:55,796
Yeah, right.

897
00:53:56,464 --> 00:53:59,216
Just be honest.
What did he actually say to you?

898
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:01,385
That's a secret
between your father and me.

899
00:54:01,469 --> 00:54:03,054
[chuckles]

900
00:54:03,137 --> 00:54:06,265
[sighs] We should have told him
ahead of time like you said.

901
00:54:06,348 --> 00:54:08,225
Then things would've gone
a bit better today.

902
00:54:08,309 --> 00:54:11,645
No. I think today
was the perfect time for this.

903
00:54:11,729 --> 00:54:14,607
We got caught without a second
to prepare or get nervous.

904
00:54:19,737 --> 00:54:20,988
Shall we walk for a bit?

905
00:54:34,043 --> 00:54:37,171
We first met in the summer,
and it's already winter now.

906
00:54:38,297 --> 00:54:40,508
So we just need
to experience spring together.

907
00:54:40,591 --> 00:54:41,592
Right?

908
00:54:41,675 --> 00:54:43,427
The very first spring we welcome together.

909
00:54:44,011 --> 00:54:45,638
How many more springs are there?

910
00:54:45,721 --> 00:54:48,432
Assuming the average lifespan is 80 years,

911
00:54:48,516 --> 00:54:49,683
about 40 more?

912
00:54:49,767 --> 00:54:50,935
Wow.

913
00:54:52,019 --> 00:54:57,316
[chuckles] Hearing that I'll be welcoming
40 springs with one person seems a bit…

914
00:54:57,399 --> 00:54:58,859
Disappointing?

915
00:54:59,443 --> 00:55:01,362
-[chuckles]
-Ah, I knew it.

916
00:55:01,987 --> 00:55:04,240
I guess I played the marriage card
a little too early.

917
00:55:04,323 --> 00:55:05,574
[chuckles]

918
00:55:07,201 --> 00:55:10,621
Tell me, Mr. Kang,
aren't you afraid of marriage?

919
00:55:11,122 --> 00:55:12,206
Yes, I am.

920
00:55:12,706 --> 00:55:15,751
Especially since I've failed
at it already. How could I not be?

921
00:55:16,752 --> 00:55:17,837
Is there a "but"?

922
00:55:18,879 --> 00:55:20,047
But it's with you.

923
00:55:23,843 --> 00:55:26,929
Because I want to see
40 seasons of cherry blossoms,

924
00:55:27,012 --> 00:55:28,430
summer fireworks,

925
00:55:28,514 --> 00:55:30,933
autumn leaves, and snowy winters with you.

926
00:55:31,559 --> 00:55:34,812
Sure, marriage can cause pain,
but it has its fair share of benefits too.

927
00:55:34,895 --> 00:55:37,523
Also, if you ever get sick
or need legal protection,

928
00:55:37,606 --> 00:55:40,025
I can officially step in
as your protector.

929
00:55:40,109 --> 00:55:42,862
And I can give you everything I own
if you need me to.

930
00:55:43,821 --> 00:55:45,197
I didn't realize that,

931
00:55:45,906 --> 00:55:48,242
but it's actually a very tempting offer.

932
00:55:48,325 --> 00:55:51,370
What's more,
I'm older than you, as you know.

933
00:55:51,453 --> 00:55:52,663
[chuckles]

934
00:55:55,124 --> 00:55:56,125
Mr. Kang.

935
00:55:59,420 --> 00:56:01,297
I really don't think

936
00:56:01,839 --> 00:56:03,215
I can choose

937
00:56:03,716 --> 00:56:05,551
option four, after all.

938
00:56:07,344 --> 00:56:10,556
So I'll just look for a place
that's within my budget.

939
00:56:12,391 --> 00:56:13,392
As for…

940
00:56:14,351 --> 00:56:16,145
your marriage proposal,

941
00:56:16,896 --> 00:56:18,606
I'll keep thinking about it.

942
00:56:20,649 --> 00:56:23,944
Then my proposal's only on hold,
not rejected.

943
00:56:24,612 --> 00:56:28,073
It's a 40-year, long-term project,
so take your time reviewing it.

944
00:56:28,657 --> 00:56:29,658
Okay.

945
00:56:31,202 --> 00:56:34,205
And when my love is overflowing,
I might just say yes

946
00:56:34,288 --> 00:56:37,499
before you even have time
to get nervous or prepare for it.

947
00:56:38,709 --> 00:56:40,294
I'll be waiting right here.

948
00:56:40,377 --> 00:56:41,587
[chuckles]

949
00:56:52,932 --> 00:56:53,933
[exhales]

950
00:57:11,867 --> 00:57:12,868
This is it!

951
00:57:13,369 --> 00:57:14,370
[exclaims]

952
00:57:14,453 --> 00:57:15,621
[clears throat]

953
00:57:15,704 --> 00:57:17,790
[breathing deeply]

954
00:57:18,958 --> 00:57:19,959
[giggles]

955
00:57:23,921 --> 00:57:25,589
[employee] Did you see this?

956
00:57:25,673 --> 00:57:28,592
[suspicious music plays]

957
00:57:47,278 --> 00:57:48,570
BLAH BLAH - ANONYMOUS ONLINE
COMMUNITY FOR PROFESSIONALS

958
00:57:48,654 --> 00:57:50,364
OFFICE AFFAIR

959
00:57:51,240 --> 00:57:55,077
[employee 1] Anyone want the scoop
on a massive affair going down at SAEUM?

960
00:57:55,160 --> 00:57:58,163
Give me enough upvotes,
and I'll drop the details.

961
00:57:59,331 --> 00:58:00,833
[typing]

962
00:58:02,501 --> 00:58:03,794
[phone buzzes]

963
00:58:06,046 --> 00:58:06,880
OFFICE AFFAIR

964
00:58:08,674 --> 00:58:10,551
[employee 2] Hurry up and spill.
The suspense is killing me.

965
00:58:10,634 --> 00:58:13,345
[employee 3] 100% agree. Who is it?
Someone's definitely sweating right now.

966
00:58:13,429 --> 00:58:15,014
[employee 4] I have my popcorn.
Hurry and spill the tea.

967
00:58:15,097 --> 00:58:17,766
[commenter] Wow. Cheating scandals from
other companies are the absolute best.

968
00:58:17,850 --> 00:58:20,561
[employee 5] Agreed! The vibe on
the eighth floor is super tense right now.

969
00:58:20,644 --> 00:58:22,062
-Maybe this is why.
-[commenter 2] SAEUM's wild.

970
00:58:22,146 --> 00:58:23,397
[Ji-yoon] An affair?

971
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,816
Someone's probably
just spinning stories again.

972
00:58:25,899 --> 00:58:29,111
[Kee-tae] Still, there's no smoke
without fire. I agree too.

973
00:58:29,194 --> 00:58:32,448
[Na-ri] I'm super curious too.
Wish they'd hurry up and tell us.

974
00:58:32,531 --> 00:58:34,658
[employee] Since everyone wants it,
here it is.

975
00:58:34,742 --> 00:58:36,076
[Kee-tae] Hey, it's up!

976
00:58:37,661 --> 00:58:39,246
SINCE EVERYONE WANTS IT,
HERE IT IS

977
00:58:39,330 --> 00:58:40,956
[employee 1] Here's something no one knew.

978
00:58:41,040 --> 00:58:44,626
SAEUM's male Manager K
and female Manager C from another team

979
00:58:44,710 --> 00:58:46,045
used to be married!

980
00:58:47,963 --> 00:58:51,467
They divorced, then crossed paths again
when Manager C got headhunted by SAEUM.

981
00:58:51,550 --> 00:58:54,261
But get this,
Manager C just got married recently.

982
00:58:54,345 --> 00:58:57,222
Since then, things between them
have been super sketchy.

983
00:58:57,306 --> 00:58:58,974
Manager C joined K's project,

984
00:58:59,058 --> 00:59:01,185
they meet privately,
and even outside of work.

985
00:59:01,268 --> 00:59:02,895
And here's the smoking gun.

986
00:59:02,978 --> 00:59:05,564
The day Manager C was in Busan
for a design expo,

987
00:59:05,647 --> 00:59:07,983
Manager K was staying at the same hotel!

988
00:59:08,984 --> 00:59:11,779
If you're suspicious, check if they were
actually married first. [chuckles]

989
00:59:11,862 --> 00:59:13,655
RECEIPTS FROM THE SAME HOTEL
ON THE SAME DAY

990
00:59:24,500 --> 00:59:27,920
[employee 6] Manager K is Kang Si-woo,
and Manager C is Choi Soo-jin, right?

991
00:59:28,003 --> 00:59:29,296
[employee 7] Those two were
actually married?

992
00:59:29,380 --> 00:59:31,924
[employee 8] So are you saying Mr. Kang
is a divorcé or a home-wrecker?

993
00:59:32,007 --> 00:59:33,926
-Which one is it?
-[employee 9] He's both!

994
00:59:34,009 --> 00:59:36,553
[employee 10] Holy crap.
I've seen them together in a car before.

995
00:59:36,637 --> 00:59:38,514
[employee 11] The vibe was weird then too.

996
00:59:38,597 --> 00:59:41,350
[employee 12] They're great at their jobs
and sleeping around too.

997
00:59:41,433 --> 00:59:44,645
[employee 13] Don't tarnish the company's
reputation and just quit together already.

998
00:59:50,150 --> 00:59:53,028
[TODAY'S HOT ISSUE]
OFFICE AFFAIR

999
00:59:53,112 --> 00:59:54,113
[phone buzzes]

1000
00:59:57,449 --> 00:59:58,826
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang,

1001
00:59:58,909 --> 01:00:00,244
I think you should see this.

1002
01:00:07,668 --> 01:00:10,254
SINCE EVERYONE WANTS IT, HERE IT
IS! HERE'S SOMETHING NO ONE KNEW

1003
01:00:10,337 --> 01:00:12,172
SAEUM'S MALE MANAGER K
AND FEMALE MANAGER C

1004
01:00:12,256 --> 01:00:13,257
FROM ANOTHER TEAM

1005
01:00:13,340 --> 01:00:14,925
RECEIPTS FROM THE SAME HOTEL
ON THE SAME DAY

1006
01:00:21,348 --> 01:00:22,641
[sighs]

1007
01:00:23,350 --> 01:00:25,436
[tense music playing]

1008
01:00:26,562 --> 01:00:28,897
-Oh.
-Mr. Kang?

1009
01:00:35,696 --> 01:00:37,364
You just stay quiet. Don't do a thing.

1010
01:00:38,991 --> 01:00:39,992
[sighs]

1011
01:00:40,951 --> 01:00:43,203
[pants] What is all this?

1012
01:00:43,287 --> 01:00:44,455
Tell me, how did this happen?

1013
01:00:45,289 --> 01:00:46,290
[sighs]

1014
01:00:48,083 --> 01:00:51,378
I need you to take immediate action
to have that post removed.

1015
01:00:51,462 --> 01:00:54,006
Since it's a third-party app,
there's nothing we can do right now.

1016
01:00:54,089 --> 01:00:55,090
But with time…

1017
01:00:55,174 --> 01:00:56,717
[Soo-jin] Who wrote that post?

1018
01:00:56,800 --> 01:00:59,386
I am going to report them immediately
for defamation.

1019
01:00:59,470 --> 01:01:01,597
Let's all take a deep breath.

1020
01:01:02,764 --> 01:01:06,059
So, is it true that you were both
in Busan on the same night?

1021
01:01:06,143 --> 01:01:10,355
That's right. I was on a business trip
with my team for a design expo.

1022
01:01:10,439 --> 01:01:12,608
I submitted those hotel receipts, yes,

1023
01:01:12,691 --> 01:01:15,068
but I never once ran into Mr. Kang
while I was there.

1024
01:01:15,152 --> 01:01:18,113
I noticed your business trip
was scheduled for Pohang, Mr. Kang.

1025
01:01:18,197 --> 01:01:20,824
I went to Busan due to
a sudden request from a buyer.

1026
01:01:20,908 --> 01:01:23,660
I simply picked
one of our company's partner hotels.

1027
01:01:23,744 --> 01:01:26,538
I had no idea where Ms. Choi stayed.
That's the truth.

1028
01:01:26,622 --> 01:01:29,625
Then is it true
that the two of you used to be married?

1029
01:01:29,708 --> 01:01:31,001
-Yes.
-Yes.

1030
01:01:32,377 --> 01:01:33,420
[groans]

1031
01:01:34,129 --> 01:01:39,176
Honestly, our strict company policy
is not to intervene in personal matters.

1032
01:01:39,676 --> 01:01:43,597
So your only option is to file
for a police investigation or a lawsuit.

1033
01:01:43,680 --> 01:01:47,100
So we just have to sit back
while the entire company gossips about us?

1034
01:01:47,184 --> 01:01:49,645
The noise will die down eventually.

1035
01:01:49,728 --> 01:01:52,022
And what if someone
spread this rumor with ill intent?

1036
01:01:53,815 --> 01:01:55,067
Who would do that?

1037
01:01:55,150 --> 01:01:57,110
Well, that's for the company to find out.

1038
01:01:57,194 --> 01:01:59,821
Internal corporate receipts
have been leaked within the company.

1039
01:01:59,905 --> 01:02:02,115
Shouldn't the Audit Team
be investigating that?

1040
01:02:03,075 --> 01:02:05,160
All right. I'll look into that.

1041
01:02:13,001 --> 01:02:14,336
[Ji-yoon] Where are you?

1042
01:02:14,419 --> 01:02:15,712
[sighs]

1043
01:02:21,009 --> 01:02:23,720
[Kee-tae] Totally groundless!
You're all writing fiction.

1044
01:02:23,804 --> 01:02:25,764
Anyone who actually knows Manager K

1045
01:02:25,847 --> 01:02:29,268
knows he's a total workaholic
who wouldn't bleed if you pricked him.

1046
01:02:31,645 --> 01:02:34,106
So you already knew
that they used to be married?

1047
01:02:35,315 --> 01:02:36,400
Mmm.

1048
01:02:36,483 --> 01:02:39,194
Wow, you're so amazing, you know that?

1049
01:02:39,820 --> 01:02:41,280
No, not really.

1050
01:02:41,905 --> 01:02:44,157
I can't do anything about this right now.

1051
01:02:44,241 --> 01:02:45,742
[employee] You're K, aren't you?
[chuckles]

1052
01:02:45,826 --> 01:02:48,829
I'm not. And just believe it
when I say it's not true. Geez.

1053
01:02:50,372 --> 01:02:52,749
I don't think this will fade away easily.

1054
01:02:52,833 --> 01:02:54,543
[No-ah] I asked a friend on the HR team,

1055
01:02:54,626 --> 01:02:57,212
and they said it's hard
to take down Blah Blah posts.

1056
01:02:59,881 --> 01:03:01,049
You know…

1057
01:03:01,967 --> 01:03:04,803
I was actually with Mr. Kang that night.

1058
01:03:04,886 --> 01:03:06,930
The night they were supposedly together?

1059
01:03:07,014 --> 01:03:08,015
Mmm.

1060
01:03:08,932 --> 01:03:11,643
A burglar broke into my place,
so he rushed back to Seoul.

1061
01:03:12,978 --> 01:03:14,813
If I'm able to clear this up,

1062
01:03:15,814 --> 01:03:17,232
it'll prove they weren't having an affair.

1063
01:03:17,316 --> 01:03:18,483
You can't be serious!

1064
01:03:20,027 --> 01:03:21,612
Why would you get involved like that?

1065
01:03:22,487 --> 01:03:25,157
If you do, you'll just end up
throwing yourself under the bus.

1066
01:03:25,240 --> 01:03:26,241
She's right.

1067
01:03:26,325 --> 01:03:29,620
Uh, when you're up for a promotion,
you shouldn't even cough the wrong way.

1068
01:03:29,703 --> 01:03:33,540
Just close your eyes, cover your ears,
and wait for the storm to pass. Got it?

1069
01:03:33,624 --> 01:03:34,708
[sighs]

1070
01:03:34,791 --> 01:03:36,835
MR. KANG, I THINK YOU SHOULD
SEE THIS - WHERE ARE YOU?

1071
01:03:36,918 --> 01:03:38,086
[coworker clears throat]

1072
01:03:40,172 --> 01:03:41,173
So what happened?

1073
01:03:42,049 --> 01:03:44,259
-What do you mean?
-Mr. Kang and Ms. Choi.

1074
01:03:44,343 --> 01:03:46,637
You're all on the task force,
so you must know something.

1075
01:03:46,720 --> 01:03:47,721
Yeah, we do know.

1076
01:03:47,804 --> 01:03:50,557
We know Mr. Kang is way too busy
to have time for an affair.

1077
01:03:50,641 --> 01:03:52,684
Come on, you don't know that.

1078
01:03:52,768 --> 01:03:55,812
No matter how busy you are,
you can still find time to sleep together.

1079
01:03:55,896 --> 01:03:59,232
She's right. You can use a business trip
as an excuse to stay in the same hotel.

1080
01:04:00,651 --> 01:04:02,194
Then you two go ahead and do that.

1081
01:04:02,277 --> 01:04:05,113
And stop running your mouths
about other people's lives.

1082
01:04:07,032 --> 01:04:09,242
Let's just go order. Yeah?

1083
01:04:09,993 --> 01:04:12,204
Uh, you can only sit after you order.

1084
01:04:13,580 --> 01:04:14,623
It's that way.

1085
01:04:15,207 --> 01:04:17,876
-Hold back. Please.
-[phone buzzes]

1086
01:04:20,629 --> 01:04:23,173
[Si-woo] I'm on my way in
after getting some fresh air.

1087
01:04:39,856 --> 01:04:41,316
So did you go to her room,

1088
01:04:41,400 --> 01:04:43,777
or did Ms. Choi come to yours instead?

1089
01:04:43,860 --> 01:04:44,861
[tense music playing]

1090
01:04:44,945 --> 01:04:47,364
I mean, why did you
even bother divorcing anyway?

1091
01:04:49,157 --> 01:04:54,329
What, you got a thing
for dangerous relationships, huh? [laughs]

1092
01:04:54,413 --> 01:04:56,039
Is this all you've got?

1093
01:04:56,123 --> 01:04:57,791
Is this how you planned to ruin me?

1094
01:04:58,625 --> 01:05:01,545
I have no idea what you mean, you know?

1095
01:05:02,754 --> 01:05:03,755
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1096
01:05:03,839 --> 01:05:05,716
You wanna hit me? Do it.

1097
01:05:05,799 --> 01:05:07,801
Yeah, hit me in front
of all these people watching.

1098
01:05:07,884 --> 01:05:09,261
Do it. Yeah.

1099
01:05:09,970 --> 01:05:13,223
Ms. Choi and Mr. Kang
weren't together that night.

1100
01:05:14,933 --> 01:05:16,893
And how could you possibly know that?

1101
01:05:17,394 --> 01:05:19,604
Because I was the one who was with him.

1102
01:05:22,023 --> 01:05:23,108
What?

1103
01:05:31,116 --> 01:05:33,452
[romantic music playing]

1104
01:05:42,377 --> 01:05:43,670
Mr. Kang and I

1105
01:05:44,588 --> 01:05:45,922
are dating.

1106
01:05:46,006 --> 01:05:47,215
[gasps]

1107
01:05:57,893 --> 01:06:00,937
Is this your answer to my proposal?

1108
01:06:10,947 --> 01:06:12,199
Yes.

1109
01:06:13,116 --> 01:06:15,118
[music continues]

1110
01:06:59,079 --> 01:07:01,498
SPECIAL THANKS TO BAE YU-RAM

1111
01:07:29,609 --> 01:07:31,444
[Ji-yoon] I thought that
by telling the truth,

1112
01:07:31,528 --> 01:07:33,280
the lies would disappear.

1113
01:07:33,363 --> 01:07:35,073
You have to brace yourself.

1114
01:07:35,156 --> 01:07:37,701
[colleague] Do you think Cha Ji-yoon
actively threw herself at him?

1115
01:07:37,784 --> 01:07:40,078
[Soo-jin] People can be crueler
than you'd think.

1116
01:07:40,161 --> 01:07:41,204
But don't let them break you.

1117
01:07:41,288 --> 01:07:42,956
Well, I'm still the same.

1118
01:07:43,039 --> 01:07:45,000
Are you able to say
with absolute certainty

1119
01:07:45,083 --> 01:07:48,461
that no personal feelings
affected that decision?

1120
01:07:48,545 --> 01:07:51,840
[No-ah] How would you feel if
I got transferred to an overseas office?

1121
01:07:51,923 --> 01:07:54,092
[Na-ri] A complaint has been filed
against Mr. Kang.

1122
01:07:54,175 --> 01:07:55,468
[Young-sam] Have you really
lost your mind?

1123
01:07:55,552 --> 01:07:57,178
[U-jin] Why's there so much noise lately?

1124
01:07:57,262 --> 01:07:59,931
About Ms. Cha, let her go.

